a settling-thickening tank.

14
00:00:44,864 --> 00:00:47,786
The treatment of settling-thickening
tank is based on sedimentation.

15
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:51,640
Faecal sludge enters the tank through
inlet at the front.

16
00:00:52,515 --> 00:00:55,575
As an outlet for the sludge is only
provided at the back end,

17
00:00:55,775 --> 00:00:58,401
the sludge has to travel
through the tank.

18
00:00:59,234 --> 00:01:03,602
During its way through the tank
dense solids settle out at the bottom.

19
00:01:05,776 --> 00:01:08,080
These solids are further compressed
by the weight

20
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:12,166
of the settled sludge layer,
as a result of these two processes

21
00:01:12,366 --> 00:01:15,014
called settling and thickening,
the sludge that settle

22
00:01:15,214 --> 00:01:17,367
at the bottom of the tank has
a higher solid content,

23
00:01:17,567 --> 00:01:20,217
and the effluent leaving the tank,
a lower solid content

24
00:01:20,417 --> 00:01:23,402
than the thicker sludge discharged
into the settling-thickening tank.

25
00:01:24,497 --> 00:01:26,625
So all settling-thickening tanks
really do

26
00:01:26,825 --> 00:01:29,836
is to separate liquids
and solids.

27
00:01:30,099 --> 00:01:33,161
Usually between 50 to 80%  of
suspended solids that are discharged

28
00:01:33,361 --> 00:01:36,036
into the settling-thickening tank
stay in the tank, 

29
00:01:36,236 --> 00:01:38,169
where as the remaining solids
stay in the effluent.

30
00:01:38,885 --> 00:01:41,809
This means that both liquids
effluent and the solids

31
00:01:42,009 --> 00:01:43,608
require further treatment.

32
00:01:43,808 --> 00:01:46,105
So what is the benefit of
a settling-thickening tank?

33
00:01:46,576 --> 00:01:48,595
Let's consider a hypothetical
example.

34
00:01:49,303 --> 00:01:52,236
This slide shows the change
of sludge volume

35
00:01:52,436 --> 00:01:54,163
as a function of the solids content.

36
00:01:54,363 --> 00:01:57,005
As you can see from the slope of
the curve

37
00:01:57,205 --> 00:02:00,248
the reduction sludge volume
is highest at low solid contents.

38
00:02:00,448 --> 00:02:04,919
Let's assume we have 1000 liters
of sludge with a solid content of 1%

39
00:02:05,119 --> 00:02:07,709
which is typical for septic
tank sludge.

40
00:02:07,909 --> 00:02:10,903
How will this volume change when
we increase

41
00:02:11,103 --> 00:02:13,974
the solid content from 1%
to 5%

42
00:02:14,174 --> 00:02:16,755
of when we increase it from
1% to 10%?

43
00:02:16,955 --> 00:02:20,315
These are typical solids contents
from settling-thickening tanks

44
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:22,627
in Accra and Dakar.

45
00:02:22,890 --> 00:02:26,244
Increased solid content would reduce
the sludge volume to 200 liters

46
00:02:26,444 --> 00:02:29,899
for 5% solids and 100 liters
for 10% solids.

47
00:02:30,740 --> 00:02:34,322
This is a reduction of the initial
volume of 80 and 90%.

48
00:02:35,378 --> 00:02:39,086
As the required space for dewatering
technologies, such as drying beds

49
00:02:39,286 --> 00:02:42,139
uses the function of the volume
of sludge that needs to be dewatered

50
00:02:42,339 --> 00:02:45,131
settling-thickening tanks can reduce
the required footprint

51
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:46,572
of sludge dewatering technologies.

52
00:02:47,325 --> 00:02:50,184
Settling-thickening tanks are
usually loaded with sludge

53
00:02:50,384 --> 00:02:51,832
for between 1 week to 1 month.

54
00:02:52,889 --> 00:02:54,737
To treat the solid content
in a settled sludge

55
00:02:54,937 --> 00:02:57,573
the sludge can be left for
thickening beyond this period. 

56
00:02:57,773 --> 00:02:59,771
This is usually done for several
days or weeks,

57
00:02:59,971 --> 00:03:02,360
as shown here for anaerobic ponds

58
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:04,910
another type of settling-thickening
technology in Dakar.

59
00:03:05,824 --> 00:03:08,333
Following this period, the sludge
that accumulates at the bottom

60
00:03:08,533 --> 00:03:10,430
requires removal before
another cycle

61
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:12,894
of loading and thickening
can be started.

62
00:03:13,766 --> 00:03:16,518
This sludge removal should be done
by pumps

63
00:03:16,718 --> 00:03:18,191
to ensure protection of workers.

64
